From: cris <cris@example.com>
Date: 2026-05-24
Subject: [PATCH] mt7530-mdio: register MDIO bus (PHYs) BEFORE dsa_register_switch

For the EN751221 MCM switch (mt7530-mdio @ phy 0x1f), the internal PHYs live
in the switch's <mdio> sub-node and are registered by mt7530_post_register()
via devm_of_mdiobus_register(). That was called AFTER dsa_register_switch(),
so when DSA connected each user port to its phy-handle the PHY device did not
exist yet -> "failed to connect to PHY: -ENODEV" on every lanN.

Register the MDIO bus first so the PHY devices exist before DSA port setup.
Mirrors the same fix applied to the mt7530-mmio probe path.
---
 gsw/mt7530-mdio.c | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/gsw/mt7530-mdio.c
+++ b/gsw/mt7530-mdio.c
@@ -212,11 +212,15 @@ mt7530_probe(struct mdio_device *mdiodev)
 	if (priv->id == ID_MT7531)
 		priv->create_sgmii = mt7531_create_sgmii;

+	ret = mt7530_post_register(priv);
+	if (ret)
+		return ret;
+
 	ret = dsa_register_switch(priv->ds);
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;

-	return mt7530_post_register(priv);
+	return 0;
 }

 static void
